###
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  MinIO Phase 0 + Phase 1 — Manual Test Suite
#  Use with VS Code REST Client extension
#
#  HOW TO RUN:
#   1. docker compose up -d minio postgres mongodb redis rabbitmq
#   2. node src/scripts/setup-minio.js    (creates buckets + lifecycle rules)
#   3. npm run start:event                 (port 3004)
#   4. Replace {{TOKEN}}, {{EVENT_ID}} with real values from the login/create steps
#
#  MinIO Console: http://localhost:9001
#  Login:         ticketbox_admin / ticketbox_secret_2026
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

@baseUrl     = http://localhost:3004
@minioUrl    = http://localhost:9000
@contentType = application/json

# ── Fill these in after running D-01 and the login step ─────────────────────
@TOKEN    = PASTE_JWT_TOKEN_HERE
@EVENT_ID = PASTE_EVENT_ID_HERE

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  GROUP D — Infrastructure Checks (run FIRST — no auth needed)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### D-01: MinIO Health Check
# Expected: HTTP 200 OK (empty body)
# Confirm: MinIO container is running and ready
GET {{minioUrl}}/minio/health/live

###

### D-02: MinIO Bucket List via S3 API
# Expected: HTTP 200 with XML listing both buckets
# Note: MinIO requires AWS Signature v4 — use the Console UI for manual browsing
# Console: http://localhost:9001  |  Login: ticketbox_admin / ticketbox_secret_2026
GET {{minioUrl}}
Authorization: AWS ticketbox_admin:ticketbox_secret_2026

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  AUTH — Get a token first (copy from test_event/event-service.http)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### AUTH-01: Login
# Expected: 200 OK with { accessToken, refreshToken }
# Copy the accessToken value into @TOKEN above
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/auth/login
Content-Type: {{contentType}}

{
  "email": "organizer@test.com",
  "password": "password123"
}

###

### AUTH-02: Create Draft Concert
# Expected: 201 Created with { event_id, status: "DRAFT", current_step: 1 }
# Copy event_id into @EVENT_ID above
POST {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  GROUP A — Image Presigned Upload (Phase 1 core feature)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### A-01: Get Presigned URL — image_url (Happy Path)
# Expected: 200 OK
# {
#   "presignedUrl": "http://localhost:9000/ticketbox-images/events/{{EVENT_ID}}/image_url_<hex8>.jpg?...",
#   "objectKey":    "events/{{EVENT_ID}}/image_url_<hex8>.jpg",
#   "expiresIn":    900,
#   "maxSizeBytes": 5242880
# }
# IMPORTANT: Copy presignedUrl and objectKey for use in A-02 and A-07
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts/{{EVENT_ID}}/upload-url?type=image_url&ext=jpg
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

###

### A-01b: Get Presigned URL — cover_image_url
# Expected: same structure, objectKey uses "cover_image_url" prefix
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts/{{EVENT_ID}}/upload-url?type=cover_image_url&ext=webp
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

###

### A-01c: Get Presigned URL — ticket_image_url (Q10 decision: reuse same endpoint)
# Expected: same structure, objectKey uses "ticket_image_url" prefix
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts/{{EVENT_ID}}/upload-url?type=ticket_image_url&ext=png
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

###

### A-04: REJECTED MIME TYPE — invalid type parameter
# Expected: 400 Bad Request
# {
#   "statusCode": 400,
#   "message": "Unsupported upload type: document_pdf. Allowed: image_url, ..."
# }
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts/{{EVENT_ID}}/upload-url?type=document_pdf&ext=pdf
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

###

### A-06: Presigned URL Endpoint — Unauthenticated (no token)
# Expected: 401 Unauthorized
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts/{{EVENT_ID}}/upload-url?type=image_url&ext=jpg

###


# ─── A-02: PUT file to MinIO (copy presignedUrl from A-01 response) ───────────
# Replace PASTE_PRESIGNED_URL_HERE with the actual presignedUrl from A-01

### A-02: Upload JPEG directly to MinIO via Presigned URL (Happy Path)
# BEFORE running: replace the URL below with presignedUrl from A-01
# Expected: 200 OK (empty body from MinIO)
# Verify: object appears in MinIO Console under ticketbox-images/events/{{EVENT_ID}}/
# IMPORTANT: For VS Code REST Client, the file must exist locally.
# Use a small test JPEG (< 5 MB).
PUT PASTE_PRESIGNED_URL_HERE
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./tests/test_minio/test_assets/sample_banner.jpg

###

### A-03: Upload OVERSIZED file (> 5 MB) — should be rejected by MinIO
# Expected: 403 Forbidden — { Code: "SignatureDoesNotMatch" }
# The presigned URL was signed with ContentLength = 5242880 (5 MB max).
# Any upload where actual bytes differ from signed ContentLength is rejected.
# Use the same presignedUrl from A-01 but send a file > 5 MB.
PUT PASTE_PRESIGNED_URL_HERE
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./tests/test_minio/test_assets/large_image_6mb.jpg

###


# ─── A-05: Expired URL test ────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# 1. Temporarily reduce TTL: set MINIO_PRESIGN_TTL_IMAGES=5 in your .env
# 2. Restart event service
# 3. Call A-01 to get a URL
# 4. Wait 10 seconds
# 5. Run this request (paste the URL from step 3):

### A-05: Expired Presigned URL
# Expected: 403 Forbidden { Code: "AccessDenied", Message: "Request has expired" }
PUT PASTE_EXPIRED_URL_HERE
Content-Type: image/jpeg

< ./tests/test_minio/test_assets/sample_banner.jpg

###


# ─── A-07: End-to-End — Use MinIO object key in Step 1 ───────────────────────
# Pre-condition: A-02 succeeded. Copy the objectKey from A-01 response.

### A-07: Save Step 1 with MinIO object key as image_url
# Expected: 200 OK { event_id, status: "DRAFT", step_completed: 1, next_step: 2 }
# Verify: MongoDB show_info.image_url = "events/{{EVENT_ID}}/image_url_<hex>.jpg"
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts/{{EVENT_ID}}/step/1
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

{
  "name": "MinIO Test Concert",
  "category": "Music",
  "address_type": "OFFLINE",
  "venue_name": "Test Arena",
  "province": "Ho Chi Minh",
  "organizer_name": "MinIO Tester",
  "image_url": "PASTE_OBJECT_KEY_FROM_A01_HERE",
  "cover_image_url": "PASTE_COVER_OBJECT_KEY_FROM_A01b_HERE",
  "description": "Testing MinIO image storage integration"
}

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  GROUP C — Regression (existing wizard must still work)
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### C-01a: Step 2 — DateTime and Tickets (no MinIO changes here)
# Expected: 200 OK { step_completed: 2, ticket_types_saved: 2 }
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts/{{EVENT_ID}}/step/2
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

{
  "start_time": "2026-12-31T20:00:00.000Z",
  "ticket_types": [
    {
      "name": "VIP",
      "price": 1500000,
      "is_free": false,
      "total_quantity": 50,
      "min_per_order": 1,
      "max_per_order": 4,
      "ticket_image_url": "PASTE_TICKET_OBJECT_KEY_FROM_A01c_HERE"
    },
    {
      "name": "GA",
      "price": 500000,
      "is_free": false,
      "total_quantity": 200
    }
  ]
}

###

### C-01b: Step 3 — Slug and Privacy
# Expected: 200 OK { step_completed: 3, next_step: 4 }
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts/{{EVENT_ID}}/step/3
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

{
  "slug": "minio-test-concert-2026",
  "privacy": "PUBLIC",
  "confirmation_message": "Thank you! MinIO test successful."
}

###

### C-01c: Step 4 — Payment and Publish
# Expected: 200 OK { status: "ACTIVE", event_url: "https://ticketbox.vn/minio-test-concert-2026" }
PUT {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts/{{EVENT_ID}}/step/4
Content-Type: {{contentType}}
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

{
  "bank_account_name": "MINIO TESTER",
  "bank_account_number": "9876543210",
  "bank_name": "BIDV",
  "bank_branch": "HCM",
  "vat_business_type": "INDIVIDUAL"
}

###

### C-02: Public Event List — verify image_url contains MinIO key (not /uploads/ path)
# Expected: 200 OK, data[0].image_url = "events/{{EVENT_ID}}/image_url_<hex>.jpg"
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/concerts?page=1&limit=5

###

### C-04: Get Draft — verify image_url persisted in MongoDB
# Expected: 200 OK, step_1.image_url = "events/{{EVENT_ID}}/image_url_<hex>.jpg"
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts/{{EVENT_ID}}/draft
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  GROUP D (continued) — Infrastructure Persistence
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

### D-03: Container Restart Persistence Test
# Step 1: Upload an image (A-02) → note the objectKey
# Step 2: Run this to restart MinIO (approve in terminal):
#   docker compose restart ticketbox-minio
# Step 3: Go to http://localhost:9001 and verify the uploaded object still exists
# (This test cannot be run via REST Client — execute in terminal)

### D-04: Nginx Proxy Connectivity
# Verify the /minio/ proxy route works through Nginx (port 3000)
# Expected: 200 OK from MinIO health check through the Nginx proxy
GET http://localhost:3000/minio/minio/health/live

###


# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#  ERROR PATH — MinIO Offline
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# To test B-09/B-10 (503 when MinIO is down):
#  1. docker stop ticketbox-minio
#  2. Run A-01 or A-01c below
#  3. Expected: 503 { error: "Storage service unavailable" }
#  4. docker start ticketbox-minio  (restore service)

### B-10: MinIO Offline — Image Presigned URL Returns 503
# (Run only after stopping MinIO container)
# Expected: 503 Service Unavailable
GET {{baseUrl}}/api/organizer/concerts/{{EVENT_ID}}/upload-url?type=image_url&ext=jpg
Authorization: Bearer {{TOKEN}}

###
